<div class="container intro">
  <div class="row justify-content-md-center align-items-center">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-5">
      <img src="assets/images/intro.jpg" class="img-fluid"/>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-5">
      <h1>I bought a 2017 Mercedes Sprinter 170" EXT 4x4. I'm converting it into an off-grid adventure van.</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container feed">
  <div class="row">
    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/solar-test-roof.jpg"
        alt="Test fitting 600W of solar on a sprinter van"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        Test fitting the solar panels. Lots of room left on either side for rails or an awning.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/sprinter-4x4-winter.jpg"
        alt="Sprinter 4x4 in the snow"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/heating-system-mounted.jpg"
        alt="Rixens heating system"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        I fit everything together out of the van first and did a few test runs to ensure I had a good understanding of how it works before trying to install it in the van. The gist of it is that a diesel fired furnace heats coolant which is circulated through a coolant-water heat exchanger for hot water, and then an air exchanger for climate control via a thermostat, and then the coolant is returned to the furnace to start the process over again.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/heating-system.jpg"
        alt="Rixens heating system"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        This complicated looking bundle of stuff will provide me with on demand hot water, climate control, and tank and water line heating in cold climates.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/flares-painted.jpg"
        alt="Flarespace flares painted white"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
