    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/flare-test.jpg"
        alt="Flarespace flares"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/flares-raw.jpg"
        alt="Flarespace flares"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        Flares are here! These will be mounted where the rearmost windows would go and will allow me to sleep across the van comfortably. They are made of fiberglass and came sanded and nearly paint ready.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/trailer.jpg"
        alt="Sprinter van with trailer"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        I picked up a 6x10 trailer to avoid keeping storage units in various places. Instead I can now leave it in the general area I'll be staying. In the long run it should be far cheaper than the $160 I was paying for storage in multiple locations.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/dynamat-floor.jpg"
        alt="Sprinter van with dynamat"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/dynamat.jpg"
        alt="Sprinter van with dynamat"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        Sound deadening. I probably don't need this stuff at all considering the insulation that I'll be using, but it can't hurt in the more crucial areas. The difference it makes is incredible.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/toilet.jpg"
        alt="Thetford cassette toilet in a sprinter van."}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        I had a hard time deciding between the different toilet types, but opted for a euro style cassette toilet. It will have a door on the driver side of the van to access the cassette.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/dashcam.jpg"
        alt="Sprinter van with garmin dashcam"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        Dashcam installed. It's wired with a relay to both accessory and live 12v. This allows the parking mode function which will continue to record after the van has turned off, but not long enough that the starter battery is drained.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/solar-plan.jpg"
        alt="Solar plan for sprinter van"}}

      <figcaption class="figure-caption">
        Initial plan for solar. I ended up with only 6 x 100W panels. The 6th 100 fit perfecly at the back behind the rear fan.
      </figcaption>
    {{/feed-entry}}

    {{#feed-entry}}
      {{feed-img
        url="assets/images/fans-opened.jpg"
